      <div class="ingredients">
        <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>2 (6-ounce) packages frozen tilapia fillets, thawed</li>
          <li>3/4 teaspoon ground cumin</li>
          <li>1/4 teaspoon fine sea salt</li>
          <li>1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper</li>
          <li>1 tablespoon fresh lime juice</li>
          <li>8 blue or yellow corn taco shells</li>
          <li>2 cups shredded lettuce</li>
          <li>1 large tomato, chopped</li>
          <li>2 green onions, thinly sliced</li>
          <li>1/2 cup shredded Monterey Jack cheese</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3>Directions:</h3>
      <ol>
          <li>Preheat the oven to 425Â°F.</li>
          <li>Arrange fish in a single layer on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.</li>
          <li>In a small bowl, mix cumin, salt and cayenne. Sprinkle evenly over both sides of fish.</li>
          <li>Bake until golden brown and flesh begins to flake, 9 to 11 minutes.</li>
          <li>Transfer fish to a medium bowl, toss with lime juice and break into small pieces.</li>
          <li>Fill warmed taco shells with fish, lettuce, tomato and green onions and top with shredded cheese.</li>

      </ol>

